	.  The Leases are in full force and effect, in good standing and free from breach or default, and Grantors are not aware of, and have not received notice of, any act or omission, which would constitute a material breach or default under any Lease or which would otherwise allow the lessor to terminate any Lease.  Grantors have good right and full power and authority to assign, convey, grant and to transfer the interests in the Leases, without consent of the lessor (or Grantors have obtained sufficient consent from the lessor).  Except as disclosed in writing to Beneficiary, there are no Royalties (as defined below) burdening or otherwise associated with such Lands.  For purposes hereof,

	

	Royalties

	

	shall mean any amount payable as a share of the product or profit from the Lands or any Minerals produced therefrom and includes without limitation, production payments, net profits interests, net smelter return royalties, landowner

	

	s royalties, minimum royalties, overriding royalties and royalty bonuses.


