vyftubfsxxqfaqvyzvvyftuDISCOVERCompaniesPeopleInvestorsFunding RoundsAcquisitionsSchoolsEventsMy SearchesMy ListsFeaturedContributeData SolutionsAboutTermsCareersSitemapEditorial Partners: TechCrunch© 2017 Crunchbase Inc.All rights reserved.WestMountain GoldOverviewTimelineContributorsTop ContributorsAdd to this ProfileContributeOverviewUpdateIPO / StockWent Public on Feb 26, 2010 / OTCMKTS:WMTNHeadquarters:Sandpoint, IDDescription:WestMountain Gold is an exploration and development company that explores, acquires and develops advanced stage mineral properties.Categories:Precious Metals, Mineral, Natural ResourcesWebsite:http://www.westmountaingold.comSocial: Company DetailsUpdateFounded:2010Aliases:WestMountain Gold, Inc.Contact:(208) 265-1717Employees:1 - 10 | None found in CrunchbaseWestMountain Gold is an exploration and development company that explores, acquires, and develops advanced stage mineral properties. 
WestMountain Gold recently acquired 100% ownership in the Terra Project, consisting of a high-grade gold system in the resource definition phase . A Technical Report was completed by Gustavson Associates on February 19, 2013 that is NI 43-101 compliant. 
According to the technical report, this high-grade gold system has the potential for significant expansion of the resourceThe Terra Project consists of 344 Alaska state mining claims covering 223 square kilometers. All government permits and reclamation plans for continued exploration through 2014 were renewed in 2010. 
WestMountain Gold, Inc. is focused on precious metal exploration in North America. 
WestMountain’s major project is the Terra project in Alaska.  The Terra project is a high grade vein system that WestMountain is developing into a low cost underground gold mine.  WestMountain is committed to developing Terra within the highest standards of stewardship for the environment and sustainability of the resource.  WestMountain is committed to bringing “no harm” to employees and contractors through a commitment to safety of its workforce. 
Gustavson Associates of Lakewood, Colorado reported an updated N I 43-101 complianttechnical report on the resource estimate on the Terra Project in Alaska of  Indicated Resources of 117,000 tonnes grading 13.25g/t and Inferred Resources of 736,000 tonnes grading 15.63 g/t.  The high grade of nature of the Terra gold deposit lends itself to near term, low cost gold production. 
WestMountain recognizes that exploration success creates shareholder value.  WestMountain will continue to expand the Terra gold resource as well as further work on the property wide targets which include an intrusive related porphyry gold target generated by talus samples. 
WestMountain’s management and technical team are experienced Alaskan geologists with an exceptional track record of exploration success. 
WestMountain is listed on the OTC QB Exchange under the symbol WMTN.
